tangata whenua
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number: 2
Definition:"people of the land", the indigenous people; the local people, the local residents of a particular place
Origin: Maori
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: NZ context; usually Maori; general and also with specific reference to a particular place within NZ
